      "content": "The logs show two distinct issues: a timeout connecting to the payment gateway and a `NameError` where a variable is missing in the catch-all logic. During peak traffic, the system is likely being overwhelmed by requests, causing the upstream payment provider to time out. To fix this, you should increase the timeout duration for the payment gateway calls and add proper logging to capture the state variable missing in the error handler. Additionally, implementing rate limiting or backpressure mechanisms will help prevent the server from becoming overwhelmed during high-traffic periods.",
